now we need to add an authentication endpoint
  - path: /login
  - expects a json body with:
    username: string
    password: string

  - to authenticate user we will use the linux "PAM" module:
```c
    #include <security/pam_appl.h>
    #include <security/pam_misc.h> 
```
  - once authenticated, we will create a secure session id and store it into session file which will be in this format:
    - filename: ./sessions/session_<id>
    - permissions: 600 (only server can read/write)
    - contents: 
```txt
id=<id>
username=alice
created_at=<timestamp>
expires_at=<timestamp>
```
  - this session id will be attached to the http cookie using the Set-Cookie response header
```txt
  Set-Cookie: session=<id>; HttpOnly; Path=/; SameSite=Lax
```
  - in further requests we will read and parse cookie and check if the session id is valid and not expired based on the expires_at timestamp
    - then, we will allow the request to proceed
    - otherwise, we will return 401 Unauthorized

as current server is multi threaded we need to keep this thread safe
